    {
      "id": "set-capabilities-contracts-overview",
      "type": "markdown",
      "label": "Why This Map Matters",
      "position": {
        "x": -1260,
        "y": 40
      },
      "width": 540,
      "height": 300,
      "color": "#1976d2",
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "markdown": "# Node Sets → Capabilities + Contracts\n\nThis is where node-set thinking stops being pure taxonomy.\n\nEach set below is mapped to:\n- the **capabilities** it pressures in the substrate\n- the **contracts** it needs to behave coherently\n\nStart with four sets:\n- planning\n- knowledge / research\n- agent / prompting\n- workflow / execution\n\nIf the same capability/contract keeps recurring, that is architecture pressure, not coincidence.",
        "_classBinding": {
          "key": "markdown",
          "sourceRef": "/library/classes/nodes/markdown.node-class.node",
          "ref": "/library/classes/nodes/markdown.node-class.node",
          "identity": {
