    {
      "id": "contracts-shared",
      "type": "markdown",
      "label": "Shared Contracts",
      "position": {
        "x": 380,
        "y": 20
      },
      "width": 460,
      "height": 1060,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "markdown": "## Shared Contracts\n\n### Planning contracts\n- required fields\n- lifecycle/status rules\n- allowed relationships\n- prompt summary priority\n\n### Knowledge / Research contracts\n- source/evidence traceability\n- claim vs fact distinction\n- citation/reference rules\n- summary fallbacks\n\n### Agent / Prompting contracts\n- tool/skill boundaries\n- handoff semantics\n- memory/result lineage\n- execution safety boundaries\n\n### Workflow / Execution contracts\n- input/output type rules\n- trigger/action ordering\n- failure path semantics\n- state transition expectations\n\n### Repeaters across sets\n- required vs optional fields\n- relationship rules\n- lifecycle/state rules\n- summary/detail/icon expectations\n\nThese repeated contracts are likely more real than any single base node class.",
        "_classBinding": {
          "key": "markdown",
          "sourceRef": "/library/classes/nodes/markdown.node-class.node",
          "ref": "/library/classes/nodes/markdown.node-class.node",
          "identity": {
