    {
      "id": "architecture-pressure",
      "type": "markdown",
      "label": "Architecture Pressure",
      "position": {
        "x": 920,
        "y": 300
      },
      "width": 420,
      "height": 340,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "markdown": "## Architecture Pressure\n\nThis map suggests a likely split:\n\n- node sets define **semantic families**\n- capabilities define **behavior/surface pressure**\n- contracts define **rules and lifecycle**\n\nThat does **not** force a grand framework yet.\n\nBut it does tell us where repeated patterns are trying to become explicit.",
